title: Barks and Purrs
creator: Colette
description:
LibriVox recording of Barks and Purrs, by Colette. Barks and Purrs is a collection of seven episodes in the lives of Toby-Dog, a French Bulldog, and Kiki-the-Demure, a Maltese cat, living in a comfortable household. The episodes cover a hot afternoon, a train ride, and what happened when dinner was late or their mistress was ill. We hear about the first fire in autumn, a heavy storm, and about a visitor in the household.
Sidonie-Gabrielle Colette-Willy was throughout her life a controversial French novelist. She published around 50 novels; the best known is "Gigi". (Summary by Availle) Dramatis personae: Kiki-the-Demure, a Maltese cat - Bob Gonzalez Toby-Dog, a French bull-dog - Troy Bond HE, master (of minor importance) - Matthew Reece SHE, mistress (of minor importance) - Roseanne Schmidt The Little Dog - rashada Narrator - Sandra G Audio edited by Availle For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording. For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org. M4B format available
